<HEADLINE>
FT  13 JAN 94 / World Stock Markets: South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Gains in gold shares masked growing fears of a turnround in foreign
sentiment. Golds rose 20 to 2,158 after Tuesday's 72-point fall, but
industrials lost 31 to 5,646 as offshore buying dried up. The overall index
shed 3 to 4,958.
