<PROFILE>_AN-EAMCUAF4FT</PROFILE>
<DATE>940113
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  13 JAN 94 / International Company News: Hongkong Land bond issue raises
Dollars 360m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LOUISE LUCAS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   HONG KONG
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Hongkong Land Holdings, Jardine Matheson group's property investment arm,
has raised USDollars 360m through a convertible bond issue to fund general
corporate requirements, including commitments from Trafalgar House and
development of the colony's Container Terminal 9.
The seven-year bond will carry a coupon of 4 per cent and a conversion price
of HKDollars 31.05 - a 15 per cent premium over the current market price.
The bond was initially planned to raise USDollars 300m, but this was lifted
to USDollars 360m. Approval is being sought to list the convertible bonds on
the London or Luxembourg stock exchange.
Mr Ian Durant, finance director of the company, said the issue was in line
with Hongkong Land's aim of diversifying sources of funding.
</TEXT>
