to 70 cents a share, or about Dollars 30m to Dollars 33m, compared with 55
cents a share, or Dollars 26.5m, in the year-ago quarter. Revenue is
expected to rise to between Dollars 356m and Dollars 366m, against Dollars
336m a year ago. The reserve, about 16 cents a share after tax, stems from a
loan made to a hotel managed by Hilton.
