<HEADLINE>
FT  13 JAN 94 / International Company News: Wall Street brokerage in
property link
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Smith Barney Shearson, the Wall Street brokerage house, has formed an
alliance with Remsen Partners, the property financing group, that will
provide funds for the US commercial property market, writes Patrick
Harverson.
Under the terms of the deal, Remsen will arrange mortgages on commercial
property funded by Smith Barney which the brokerage firm will eventually
sell as mortgage-backed securities. to investors.
The two partners said that they had already put together more than Dollars
100m in mortgage loans, and they expected the venture to generate as much as
Dollars 1bn in financing before the end of the year. For Smith Barney, owned
by Travelers, the insurance and financial services group, the aim of the
alliance is to boost its presence in the huge large US mortgage-backed
securities market by linking up with Remsen's network of property owners and
mortgage bankers.
Last year, Smith Barney was only ranked 15th among underwriters of mortgage
deals in the US, even though the firm is was the second largest brokerage
house in the US.
The appeal of the alliance to Remsen is the speedy fast access the private
partnership it will get to Smith Barney's capital and the ability to win
business on the back of the brokerage firm's name.
</TEXT>
