<DATE>940113
</DATE>
<HEADLINE>
FT  13 JAN 94 / UK Company News: Goode Durrant rises after realignment
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW BOLGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Shares in Goode Durrant rose by 10p to 151p yesterday after the industrial
holding company said improvements resulting from the realignment of
activities were beginning to show through.
Pre-tax profits jumped from Pounds 1.8m to Pounds 4.29m in the six months to
October 31 including a Pounds 400,000 exceptional credit from the sale of
the Laidlaw motor distribution subsidiary to Quicks last June. Sales fell
from Pounds 90.6m to Pounds 58.1m mainly due to the sale.
Mr Michael Waring, chief executive, said that Northgate, the core commercial
vehicle hire business, had doubled pre-tax profits to Pounds 3m. Utilisation
rates had increased marginally to 92 per cent, and rates had firmed as
customers, who were overwhelmingly business users, increased their activity
levels.
Northgate had successfully integrated two small acquisitions announced in
October, Trukvan Rental and Bowey Hire. It was a priority to extend the
network nationally, both organically and by acquisition.
The equipment hire division made a pre-tax profit of Pounds 279,000,
compared with a loss of Pounds 174,000 previously, and the Ravenstock
business had returned to profit.
Rawlings, the housebuilding and construction business which has been
earmarked for disposal, made pre-tax profits of Pounds 134,00, compared with
a Pounds 179,000 loss.
Earnings per share to rose 5.8p (2.3p). Stripping out the exceptional,
earnings rose to 5p. The interim dividend is increased to 2.2p (2.15p).
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Goode Durrant.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P6719 Holding Companies, NEC.
</IN>
<XX>
Types:-
</XX>
<TP>FIN  Interim results.
</TP>
<PUB>The Financial Times
</PUB>
