<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JAN 94 / World Stock Markets: Mexico
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mexican equities had recovered most of Monday's substantial losses by
yesterday's close as concern about the recent spate of rebel activity began
to abate.
The IPC index was quoted 95.45 points, or 3.9 per cent, up at 2,554.56 -
this followed a 6.3 per cent drop during the previous session, which was the
biggest one-day percentage fall since October 1989.
Some 146.6m shares were traded and advances outstripped declines by 84 to
22.
