FT  12 JAN 94 / International Company News: Wall Street broker in alliance
with Remsen
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PATRICK HARVERSON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Smith Barney Shearson, the Wall Street brokerage house, has formed an
alliance with Remsen Partners, the property financing group, that will
provide funds for the US commercial property market.
Remsen will arrange mortgages on commercial property funded by Smith Barney
which the brokerage firm will sell as mortgage-backed securities to
investors. The two partners said yesterday they had put together more than
Dollars 100m in mortgage loans, and expected the venture to generate as much
as Dollars 1bn in financing before the end of the year.
For Smith Barney, which is owned by Travelers, the insurance and financial
services group, the aim of the alliance is to lift its presence in the large
US mortgage-backed securities market by linking up with Remsen's network of
property owners and mortgage bankers. Last year, Smith Barney was ranked
15th among underwriters of mortgage deals in the US, even though the firm
was the second largest brokerage house in the US.
The appeal of the alliance to Remsen is fast access to Smith Barney's
capital and the ability to win business on the back of the brokerage firm's
name.
