FT  12 JAN 94 / International Company News: Toys R Us announces Dollars 1bn
share buy-back
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD TOMKINS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Toys R Us, the biggest US toy retailer, yesterday announced it would open 45
new toy stores in the US and 70 stores overseas this year.
It has also signed franchise agreements covering Saudi Arabia and the Gulf
emirates, and is to buy back up to Dollars 1bn worth of its shares over the
next several years.
The shares rose by Dollars  3/8 to Dollars 38 3/4 yesterday. Analysts said
the store-opening programme was in line with expectations and the share
buy-back plan would have a relatively small impact on earnings per share.
Toys R Us has 581 stores in the US and 234 overseas, so the number of
overseas stores will increase proportionally much more than the number of
domestic stores.
Part of the plan consists of signing franchise agreements which will bring
the Toys R Us name to markets that would not otherwise have been entered for
many years.
Two agreements have been signed: one with an unnamed Saudi Arabian company
for toy stores in Saudi Arabia, and another with Al Futtain Sons, a company
based in the United Arab Emirates, for stores in the UAE, Qatar, Bahrain,
Oman and Kuwait.
