development facilities by ploughing FFr80m into the construction of a new
research centre at Montpellier, saw net profits fall to an estimated FFr30m
last year from FFr38m in 1992.
Mr Chauvin said he expected acquisitions to contribute to a sharp increase
in turnover this year, with sales rising to about FFr580m against an
estimated FFr345m for 1993.
