<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JAN 94 / Observer: Pots and kettles
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The London Evening Standard clearly relishes the Tory party's current moral
squirming. Yesterday it carried a conventional advertisement for Qantas,
which by the final edition had been replaced by a 'reader offer' advertising
a two-night stay and 'gastronomic dining' at a French hotel, the Chateau
Tilques.
On the same page was a large feature on Tory MP David Ashby, who has
admitted sharing a bed at the same chateau with a male friend. Stewart
Steven, the paper's editor, says the juxtaposition was 'not entirely
coincidental. Our readers read about this wonderful hotel where our MPs go,
and they can now sample it themselves'.
</TEXT>
