<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JAN 94 / People: Mobil in the UK
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
John Banfield, a career executive with Mobil Oil, is to take over as
chairman of the UK arm of the US-based company. He will succeed Geoffrey
Cardinal, who moves on to Mobil Egypt. A Cambridge graduate, Banfield has
spent most of his career in marketing. Overseas stints have included
postings in New York, Cyprus, the Netherlands and Germany, where he is a
manager at the marketing and refining division in Hamburg.
